<br>
1) bleed = bad style, bleed breaks mez<br>
<br>
2) no hit bonus = bad.  warriors can overcome this partly with huge weaponskill, we cannot.  conquer is a prime example of this.  i cannot even estimate the number of times i have wiffed with conquer on mezd targets, fleeing casters, anything.  additionally, you should not be able to wiff on a mezzd or stunned target.  <br>
<br>
3) provoke is the only viable anytime style in hammer and it taunts, skalds do not want to taunt<br>
<br>
4) the only stun styles in midgard are based off a block.  skalds cannot spec sheild.<br>
<br>
overall, what skalds need is a new weaponspec.  so without further ado, i have tracked down something i made up previously:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showMessage?topicID=582.topic" target="top">clicky</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
and for those who are lazy:<br>
<br>
edit:  went through and increased secondary snares to be more in line with exisiting effects<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>2 hand only.  but allowing any 2hand mid weapon - axe, hammer, sword, or spear.  pick some name for it ... for this post i'll call it midgard 2h spec (M2H).  obviously with this you would have no use for a shield at all.  so if you wanted to be ONLY a 2h skald, which the vast majority of skalds are, this would be for you.  otherwise, spec in one of the 3 existing weapon lines.  the option of going 1h will be the sacrifice in exchange for a skald specific weapon spec allowing any damage type.<br>
<br>
parry is our main defensive ability.  so there's going to be a parry reactionary chain.  we can evade, there will be an evade reactionary.  bleed breaks our mez, so there will be no bleed effect on any of the styles.  and let's make the 50 spec style a whopper.  if you're giving up both the 44 DD and the 46 damage add to spec 50 weapon, there should be a damn good return for it.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>this should be viewed as a rough draft. </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> i have gone over it a couple of times seeking stupidity, overpowerings, what have you.  this should be a solid rough draft.  here we go:<br>
