high bonus to hit<br>
medium endurance use<br>
very high defensive bonus<br>
effect: 50% increased chance (not 50% chance) to parry/evade/block next attack<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>level 21</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
reactionary to you evade<br>
very high damage bonus (75%)<br>
high bonus to hit<br>
low endurance use<br>
medium defensive bonus<br>
effect: enemy attack speed penalty (10%)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>level 25</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
followup to level 10 anytime<br>
high damage bonus (60%)<br>
low bonus to hit<br>
medium endurance use<br>
no defensive adjustment<br>
effect: 3 second stun<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>level 29</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
followup to level 12 parry chain<br>
very high damage bonus (75%)<br>
very high to hit bonus<br>
medium endurance use<br>
low defensive penalty<br>
effect: enemy attack speed penalty (25%)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>level 34</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
back positional<br>
high damage bonus (60%)<br>
high to hit bonus<br>
medium endurance use<br>
high defensive penalty<br>
effect: target snared (75%)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>level 39</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
anytime<br>
low bonus damage (35%)<br>
medium to hit bonus<br>
high endurance use<br>
no defensive adjustment<br>
effect: 100% chance (based on level) to break through bladeturn in a similar fashion to perforate artery.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>level 44</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
followup to level 29 parry chain (3rd in chain)<br>
very very high damage bonus (90%)<br>
very high chance to hit<br>
high endurance use<br>
high defensive penalty<br>
effect:  DD proc 85 base damage (think reaver)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>level 50</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
followup to level 34 back positional<br>
very high damage bonus (75%)<br>
high chance to hit<br>
high endurance use<br>
low defensive penalty<br>
effect: nine second stun<br>
<br>
<br>
the above style set gives you tons of options.  no bleed so you dont break mez.  only overpowered stun is a followup to back positional, hibs get this with just straight back positional.  freedom from the tyrrany of no hit bonus &quot;styles&quot;, if you would call the insult that is them a style.  i think this would really help us as a class.  it's really tough to overpower a style set with reactionaries and positionals, and if you look above there's no doublefrost equivalent in sight.  also the majority of these styles are medium or high endurance use so a solo skald would be going oop in short order.<br>
<br>
i have tried REALLY HARD to make a *good* style set, but not a *too good* style set.<br>
